extends layout

block content
  h1 Palindrome Checker
  form(method="POST" action="/")
    label(for="userText") Enter your text here:
    br
    input(type="text" id='userText' name='userText' value=`${phrase}`)
    br
    br
    button(type="submit") Submit
  if message
    p=message
  p A Palindrome is when a word or phrase can be read both forwards and backwards
  p examples: aibohphobia (aiboh|p|hobia) , madam (ma|d|am), noon (no|on)